When calling Calendar().to_ical() it appears the the escaping rules are not applied over the vText fields where they are if vText.to_ical() is called directly.

Hence Calendar().from_ical(source).to_ical() != source.

Is there a bug in Contentline.from_parts()? Should it be checking " if values and isinstance(values, basestring):" rather than " if values and not isinstance(values, basestring):"? As it is the call to values.to_ical() will be skipped and the escape characters will not be included.

```
def from_parts(parts):
    "Turns a tuple of parts into a content line"
    (name, params, values) = parts
    try:
        if values and not isinstance(values, basestring):
            if hasattr(values, 'to_ical'):
                values = values.to_ical()
        if params:
            return Contentline('%s;%s:%s' % (name, params.to_ical(), values))
        return Contentline('%s:%s' %  (name, values))
    except:
        raise ValueError(
            'Property: %s Wrong values "%s" or "%s"' % (repr(name),
                                                        repr(params),
                                                        repr(values)))
```

